description:
My name is Jake. My wife and I reached Barista F.I.R.E. in 2023 at the age of 37.

title: Intelligent Stock Investing
description:
This channel is about helping you become a better stock market investor so you can reach financial freedom sooner - It's not about using the stock market for gambling or speculation.

Here we'll talk about the value investing fundamentals of Warren Buffett and Charlie Munger and other super investors that follow a value investing approach to investing in the stock market.

Stocks represent an ownership interest in a business. Behind every stock is a business - and if the business does well, so will the stock. However, even the most amazing business can be a bad investment if you pay too much for it. To make good stock investments it's important to pay a sensible price. Value Investors calculate the intrinsic value of a company and then look to buy it on the open stock market when prices are favourable. 

Disclaimer: This is educational content and not financial advice. Do your own due diligence and consult an expert before you take any action on the content you find on this channel.

description: Thanks for checking out The Investor Channel! I'm an individual investor for over 20 years. I studied economics and business in college. title: The Investor's Podcast Network
description:
Since 2014, we have been guiding investors and business people of all levels on how to grow financially and personally. Our flagship show, We Study Billionaires, is the largest stock investing podcast in the world, with more than 185 million downloads.

Our newest show, The Intrinsic Value Podcast, takes things one step further. Every week, we break down a fascinating business model, from Google to John Deere, teach you about the company‚Äôs competitive advantages and challenges, and then go through different valuation approaches to estimate its intrinsic value per share.

We condense dozens of hours of investment research into a single episode, helping you get a little smarter about business and investing. And if we think the stock is attractively priced after having broken it down, we add it to our Intrinsic Value Portfolio of long-term stock holdings that we build out on the show over time.

Embark on this journey into intrinsic-value investing with us!

title: The Trend-Aware Investor
description:
Welcome to my YouTube channel! Here, we dive into the world of technical analysis, focusing on stock price movements and the dynamics between buyers and sellers. Instead of relying on news or company fundamentals, we examine actual stock movements to understand market behavior.

Technical analysis helps us avoid holding onto stocks during downturns based on hope rather than data. For example, even if Tesla reports stellar earnings, its stock can decline due to factors like institutional investors reallocating portfolios or market concerns about future growth.

We identify key support and resistance levels on stock charts, marking where buyers and sellers dominate. This method allows us to capitalize on market swings by aligning with the market's direction, minimizing risk, and maximizing potential gains.

Join us as we uncover hidden signals within stock charts, helping you navigate the market with confidence. Subscribe and hit the notification bell for updates. Happy trading!

title: Prophet Market
description:
Are you interested in learning about the Stock Market?

Where should you Start? What is a Stock in the first Place?

This doesn‚Äôt have to be complicated. A Stock is simply a representation of ownership in a company. Publicly traded stocks are shares of public companies. Publicly traded companies are traded on stock exchanges and investment in their stock is open to any and everyone. The public price of these stocks fluctuates and changes every day. Investors buy these shares in hopes that in the future they will appreciate in value and make the investor a profit.

I will be posting many more videos that will go into further detail about the exchanges, trading, stock options, Investing, trading psychology and much more.

Prophetmarket123@gmail.com

title: Costa Rica Matt - Real Estate Guidance
description:
I provide in-depth analysis of the Costa Rica real estate market with the goal of empowering clients to make the best possible decisions. I first came to Guanacaste in 2008 as a Peace Corps volunteer and service continues to define my business.

Since then I've directed non-profit organizations, built a small Costa Rican homestead and started a family with my wife, complete with two "Guanacasteco" sons born here in this beautiful country.

I started working in real estate eight years ago; in October 2017 I became a full time Realtor and joined the team at Coldwell Banker Tamarindo Realty. I have been thrilled to help dozens of foreigners and Costa Ricans transition to the "pura vida life" in northwestern Guanacaste (or transition back to their homes) through real estate.

Visit www.coldwellbankerpacificrealty.com to learn more about our brokerage.

No legal advice!

title: Stock Niti
description:
At Stock Niti, we focus on disciplined stock trading, emphasizing a probability-based approach over options trading. Our philosophy is that trading isn‚Äôt about being right every time, but about managing risk and reward. We aim for a risk-reward ratio of at least 1:4, meaning the potential gains on winning trades should significantly outweigh losses. By winning just two trades out of ten, traders can still be profitable.
We use an institutional volume strategy, tracking stocks with heavy institutional investor activity. This helps us align with market momentum and make informed decisions. Our approach prioritizes risk management, capital preservation, and emotional discipline. We teach traders to be patient, wait for optimal setups, and stick to their strategies, improving long-term success. By following these principles, traders can enhance their probability of profitability while managing inevitable losses.

title: Renner Stock Farms
description:
Welcome to Renner Stock Farms! 

I am Jon Renner, a 7th generation farmer from Belleville, IL. My grandpa, Tom Renner, and my uncle, Jake Renner make up the 5th and 6th generation of our farm's legacy. Throughout watching these videos you will get to know them very well. I am starting this channel to give a unique perspective on how a grain farm works in southern Illinois. 

You may have seen our farm on RFDTV, Machinery Pete, or Heritage Iron Magazine. All three of them have stopped by on several occasions to take tours, or to see what new things we have added to our collection. Our farm also houses a large collection of horse-drawn equipment, antique tractors, and muscle tractors. 

Throughout the process of building this channel, I would like to take you through the collection and show you the ins and outs of our farm. 

Thanks for stopping by and I will see you on the next one!

title: Longer Term Implications on Trading/Investing After CoronaVirus Crisis? üò©
description:
üî¥ Trading is Risky! 70% to 89% of retail investors lose money!  Financial-Spread-Betting.com is where betting and finance meets, on the trading floor.  This is a place where we can inform, and educate little, and hopefully entertain a little too.

Spread betting is an efficient way to trade the financial markets as you pay no stamp duty or CGT on any profits you make. This is because the activity is regulated as gambling, as opposed to investing, which means spread traders don't normally pay taxes on their winnings.  The flipside of this is that with spread betting you cannot offset losses against your profits for capital gains tax purposes.

Leverage can amplify both your gains and losses since they are calculated based on the total exposure of the trade, not merely the margin needed to initiate it. Consequently, losses and profits could far outweigh your margin, so always ensure you‚Äôre trading within your means.
